John Vaughn is sworn to interpret for the defendant.
The State moves to amend the charge to disorderly conduct, contrary to Section 947.01(1) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge.  Convicted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for twelve (12) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Pay $400.00 restitution to Christian Amador-Bower at 1220 St. Clair Avenue, Sheboygan, WI 53081 within the first 60 days of probation;
2) Pay court costs;
3) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
4) no contact with Christian Amador-Bower;
5) maintain fulltime employment or work search;
6) spend one (1) day in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 06-05-16 at 5:00 p.m.  Court authorizes transfer to Sheboygan County Jail or travel outside Manitowoc County for employment purposes is authorized;
7) spend nine (9) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed and the agents discretion and upon order of the court;
8) provide DNA sample.
Minutes.
